<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
3 STUDENTS SEEK COLLEGE BOARD POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN McALPINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three students have announced their candidacies for student representative to 
the Ventura County Community College District governing board. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura College student John Scherling and Moorpark College students Lauren 
Eaton and Jon Runyan will compete for the position in elections April 4 and 5. 
</P>
<P>
Scherling, a first-year student at Ventura College, has been active in student 
government, serving as representative to both the California Student Assn. of 
Community Colleges and the Student Advisory Committee for the California 
Post-Secondary Education Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Eaton attends day and evening classes at Moorpark College while working as 
co-owner of a photography studio. She serves as public relations officer and 
executive board member of Moorpark College's Associated Student Board. 
</P>
<P>
Runyan plans to graduate from Moorpark with a degree in 
math/physics/engineering. He has served on committees for the California 
Student Assn. of Community Colleges. He also serves as executive board member 
of the Associated Student Board for Moorpark College. 
</P>
<P>
The student representative of the three-college district is recognized as a 
full member of the board and may cast an advisory vote on board business. 
</P>
<P>
The new representative will be sworn in July 3 and will serve a one-year term. 
KEN McALPINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
