<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : PAUMA VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were killed when their vehicle struck another vehicle and rammed a tree 
on California 76, just east of Nate Harrison Grade Road, 
</P>
<P>
The crash occured at 8:45 p.m. Saturday and killed the driver, Juan Lopez Rizo, 
24, and his passenger, Rodolfo Saldana, who was in his 20s, said Deputy Coroner 
Cal Vine. Both men were from Temecula. 
</P>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol said Rizo's vehicle was westbound on California 
76 and apparently drifted into the eastbound lane, where it collided with a car 
driven by Felipe Carrillo, also of Temecula. Rizo's vehicle then crossed back 
over the highway, went off the side and hit a tree. 
</P>
<P>
Carrillo was taken to Palomar Medical Center in Escondido with moderate 
injuries. 
</P>
