<P>
REDISTRIBUTING FOREIGN AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. foreign aid is stingy? Nonsense! Over the past few decades, America gave 
Israel more than $45 billion in foreign aid. No benefits were realized by the 
U.S. For the past 2 years, U.S. aid funded the human rights violations 
perpetrated by Israelis against Palestinians. 
</P>
<P>
The largest recipients of foreign aid receive the aid year after year. What 
plans do those nations have to become independent of U.S. aid? Reallocating aid 
now will: 
</P>
<P>
Help the emerging democracies; jolt the largest recipients into the realization 
that U.S. foreign aid is not an entitlement program, and provide the President 
with the flexibility and authority to effectively allocate aid funds. 
</P>
<P>
Under-funding is not the problem. The problem is ineffective distribution of 
foreign aid by Congress. 
</P>
<P>
DON BOWERS 
</P>
<P>
El Segundo 
