SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : LAKESIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eleven teen-agers riding in a pickup truck were thrown from it -- but none 
received major injuries -- at Interstate 8 at Lake Jennings Park Road, the 
California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
The truck was heading westbound at 1 a.m. Sunday when the driver, John Batts, 
19, of El Cajon, leaned over his shoulder to tell the passengers riding in the 
bed of the pickup to quiet down, the CHP said. The vehicle hit the asphalt curb 
alongside the freeway and overturned down an embankment. 
</P>
<P>
Several of the teen-agers, including Batts, were taken to Grossmont Hospital, 
where officials said they were treated for minor injuries and released. 
