<P>
Eastwood Sues Tabloid: Actor Clint Eastwood has filed a $20-million lawsuit 
against the Globe, accusing the supermarket tabloid of fabricating a front-page 
story headlined, "Clint's Life Threatened by Nazi Cult." Eastwood's lawsuit, 
filed in Los Angeles Superior Court, contends that the tabloid's Jan. 1 story, 
featuring a photo of Eastwood holding a handgun, has put the actor's life in 
danger. The Globe story says a group called the Aryan Nation had put a $100,000 
bounty on Eastwood's life because the actor refused to speak at the 
organization's convention in Washington. CLAUDIA PUIG and GREG BRAXTON 
