<P>
RETIRED JUSTICE TO JOIN L.A. LAW FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Retired state Supreme Court Justice Marcus M. Kaufman will join a Los Angeles 
law firm in June, the firm announced. 
</P>
<P>
Kaufman, 60, a 1987 appointee of Gov. George Deukmejian, resigned from the 
court effective Jan. 31, but is remaining to complete work on cases in which he 
participated. Deukmejian appointed Justice Armand Arabian to replace him. The 
firm of Buchalter, Nemer, Fields &amp; Younger said Kaufman would be involved 
in appellate matters, provide litigation strategy and technical knowledge, and 
take part in education programs for the firm's 170 lawyers. Kaufman "brings a 
wealth of experience to bear on California judicial matters at the highest 
levels," said Jack Samet, head of the firm's litigation department. 
</P>
