<P>
ROLLER COASTER COLLISION INJURES 40 RIDERS AT PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KANSAS CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 40 riders suffered minor injuries when one roller coaster train ran into 
the rear of another Saturday, officials of the Worlds of Fun amusement park 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The most serious injury reported by medical personnel at the park was a broken 
nose. Adults and children on the ride also suffered cuts and facial bruises, 
and some complained of whiplash. 
</P>
