<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOP POLITICAL UNIT SHUNS WILSON'S BID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Republican Assembly, the largest and most conservative 
grass-roots endorsing body in state GOP politics, shunned the candidacy of U.S. 
Sen. Pete Wilson for governor Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The assembly instead voted, 170 to 78, to issue no endorsement for governor and 
"a vote of no confidence" in Wilson. 
</P>
<P>
The conservative group cited Wilson's pro-choice stance on abortion as the 
principal issue defeating his bid. But Wilson was also criticized for 
"anti-free enterprise" environmental votes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
