<P>
Fed Votes Steady Credit Policy: The Federal Reserve voted to hold interest 
rates steady at its meeting in February, saying inflation was under control, 
according to just-released minutes of the meeting. The February meeting 
occurred as concerns about inflation were heightening, mostly because of a 
surge in energy prices that has since abated. Consumer prices rose about 4.6% 
last year, compared to 4.4% in 1988. 
</P>
