AARP Closing Credit Union: The American Assn. of Retired Persons said it plans 
to close its 2-year-old credit union because of a lack of interest from its 
members. AARP, the nation's largest organization for older Americans, said all 
savings would be protected in the phase-out, which still must be approved by 
the credit union's 90,000 members. 
