<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE WEEK OF MARCH 26: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Law Firm Accused of Wrongful Firing: The prominent Los Angeles law firm of 
Latham &amp; Watkins was sued in Los Angeles Superior Thursday by a former 
paralegal who claims that she was fired for "blowing the whistle" about the 
firm's alleged overbilling. 
</P>
<P>
Robyn R. Devereaux said she was terminated after two years because she told the 
firm's clients, opposing attorneys and a federal judge about alleged 
overbilling by Latham in litigation over the DuPont Plaza Hotel fire in Puerto 
Rico. Steven Stanwyck, the law firm's attorney, said the allegations are 
groundless and called Devereaux a convicted felon who has other actions pending 
against the firm. (Filed March 29, Case No. C756772) 
</P>
</TEXT>
