<P>
Southmark Sets Deal With Creditors: Southmark Corp., a Dallas-based real estate 
holding company that filed for bankruptcy protection last July, said its 
unsecured creditors agreed on a new reorganization plan calling for a quicker 
payout to creditors than the company offered in its original reorganization 
proposal. The agreement, to be filed with the U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Dallas, 
also restructures some securities and proposes a reduction in payout to 
Southmark's equity holders, the company said. 
