<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
CITY MAY BUY SITE FOR ELDERLY HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday will consider buying property for apartments for 
low-income senior citizens. 
</P>
<P>
The owner, First Lutheran Church of Fullerton, is willing to sell the 
23,800-square-foot site on East Amerige Avenue for about $750,000, said Terry 
M. Galvin, the city's redevelopment manager. 
</P>
<P>
A few old houses, including a rare two-story Victorian house, and a small 
apartment are on the property now. The city and the church would share the cost 
of finding new homes for current renters, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The city would try to find someone to buy and move the Victorian house because 
of its historical value, Galvin said. 
</P>
<P>
The council will consider signing an option to buy the property and authorizing 
its staff to find a developer to build the apartment building. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton would sell the property at a low price with the condition that rents 
forever be kept affordable to low-income seniors, Galvin said. TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
