P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
CONSTRUCTION SPENDING UP 2.6% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction spending rose 2.6% in February, the government said today, as 
unusually warm weather continued across much of the nation. 
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department said residential, non-residential and government 
construction spending totaled a seasonally adjusted annual rate of $436.5 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
That compared with a revised 2.5% gain the previous month, the warmest January 
on record. January spending was first reported last month to have rise 1.8%. 
</P>
<P>
Spending in December, the fourth-coldest since the government began keeping 
records 96 years ago, had slipped 0.3%. 
</P>
<P>
The total construction spending figure was up 4.8% from the level of building a 
year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
