<P>
800 MEET TO HONOR SAMMY DAVIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 800 actors, dancers and comedians attended a luncheon in Beverly Hills to 
honor Sammy Davis Jr. for his contribution to the world of dance. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, 64, whose condition was diagnosed as cancer in September, 1989, was 
unable to attend and is recuperating at home. 
</P>
<P>
His wife, Altovise, on Sunday accepted the annual Gypsy Award from the 
Professional Dancers Society on his behalf. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm still a gypsy at heart and of all the tributes that Sammy has received 
this is the one he would have really liked to be at," said Altovise, a former 
dancer. 
</P>
<P>
Among those attending were Patrick Swayze, Debbie Allen, Milton Berle, Janet 
Leigh, Nancy Sinatra Jr., Ken Berry and the Nicholas Brothers. 
</P>
<P>
The event featured footage of Davis' career from vaudeville to the Las Vegas 
stage to Hollywood films. 
</P>
