<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARGAUX BARES ALL TO GET HOLLYWOOD'S ATTENTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Life in the fast lane destroyed Margaux Hemingway's film career just as it was 
getting under way a decade ago, but now, at 35, the granddaughter of the late, 
great author says she is ready to come back. 
</P>
<P>
And the best way to get Hollywood's attention, she figured, was to pose nude. 
</P>
<P>
The model-actress is featured in Playboy's current edition. If nothing else, 
she proved she is in great shape. 
</P>
<P>
She insists that everything else is in order too, claiming victory in her 
battle against alcohol and cocaine dependencies. 
</P>
<P>
Hemingway was a giddy 19-year-old when she burst on the national scene as an 
ingenue in "Lipstick." The movie was terrible, but she captured the country's 
imagination. 
</P>
<P>
A fresh-faced, outdoor girl from Ketchum, Ida., Hemingway was a delightfully 
candid, naive newcomer whose love of life catapulted her into celebrity. She 
adorned the cover of Time magazine. 
</P>
<P>
After all, this was Ernest Hemingway's granddaughter. 
</P>
<P>
She signed a $1-million contract to promote a perfume and toured the world. She 
made movies -- "Killer Fish," "A Fistful of Chopsticks" and "Over the Brooklyn 
Bridge" -- none of which was very good. 
</P>
<P>
She was married and divorced twice, moving her home from New York to Venezuela 
to Paris and leading a fast-paced life that was going nowhere. 
</P>
<P>
Her second marriage -- to Venezuelan documentary film producer Bernard Foucher 
-- finally hit the rocks, and Hemingway all but disappeared. 
</P>
<P>
About 2 1/2 years ago she spent a month in the Betty Ford Clinic in Rancho 
Mirage, Calif., and has been sober since. She also lost 75 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Last year she completed a movie in Paris, "Love in C Minor," and hopes it will 
lead to a revived acting career in Hollywood, where she lives. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm single and in charge of my own life for the first time," she said. "It's a 
marvelous feeling." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Margaux Hemingway 
</P>
