<TEXT>
<P>
Laid-back singer Jimmy Buffett thought Sen. Bob Graham (D-Fla.), looked too 
formal over the weekend at a Capitol Hill meeting with 125 young leaders from 
Florida. So Buffett, a friend of the senator who calls himself "the 
non-conformist in Bob Graham's life," pulled out a pair of scissors and snipped 
off the tie, which was decorated with small Florida emblems. Buffett also spoke 
seriously, telling the crowd to get involved in their communities and recalling 
how Graham had first inspired his work to save the Florida manatee. 
