<P>
CENTRAL WASHINGTON COACH QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ELLENSBURG, Wash. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Veteran Central Washington University basketball Coach Dean Nicholson resigned 
today after an internal review found that some money raised through basketball 
camps was improperly given to student athletes. 
</P>
<P>
Nicholson, 63, has coached at Central Washington for 26 years and is one of 
only 17 college coaches to reach 600 lifetime victories. He said his 
resignation as coach and as a professor of physical education was effective 
immediately. 
</P>
<P>
An anonymous whistle-blower had complained that income generated by a 
basketball camp was distributed to student athletes at Central in violation of 
state and federal regulations, the university said in a news release. 
</P>
